The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Thursday, January 02, 2003 				 The storytellers art
				 				 				 				The modern French painter, Maurice Denis, made a statement which has now gained an aphoristic value: Remember, that a picture, before being a horse, a nude, or some kind of anecdote, is essentially a flat surface covered with colours in a certain order. Veteran artist-essayist-childrens story writer-all rolled-into-one, Badri Narains simple and colourful canvases are visually delightful. There is a child-like simplicity and harmony in his works which are loaded with layers of meanings. Each of Narains canvases tells a story and they all have an old-world charm of miniature aka album paintings and glow with the artists inner warmth. 																								When: Till January 10 (except Sunday): 3 pm - 7 pm																								Where: Gallerie 88
